The paper discusses the impact of data cleaning on downstream machine learning models, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a benchmark for joint data cleaning and machine learning experiments, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
